flowRoot.flowPara: You will be given 7 different scenes. For each scene you will have to push the green box into the green circle (goal region) by moving the robot hand. The green box is in the goal region when all four corners of box are in the circle. The controls are as follows:
Moving left or forward in this situation is considered an invalid move because you're pushing the green box into another object.
Moving in any direction in this situation is considered a valid move. The robot hand can move two or more objects at once if the objects are not colliding.

The hand will not move when you hold down a key; it will move with every key press. The box above the instructions will update with the validity of your move. If you would like to reset the scene hit the "Reset Scene" button. Once you've successfully pushed the green box into the green circle, click the "Next Scene" button to go to the next scene. Thank you for participating in this study!
